Dutch chemical group AkzoN.V. &lt;AKZO.AS> said it agreed to take over household productsubsidiaries of French group Rhone-Poulenc &lt;RHON.PA> for anundisclosed sum.    Under the agreement, Akzo will acquire the householdproduct activities of the Lyons-based &lt;Rhodic> andRemalard-based &lt;Buhler-Fontaine> units of Rhone Poulenc.Together, these activities account for over 180 mln Frenchfrancs in annual sales and employ 170, Akzo said.    Akzo will integrate the firms, to be partially joined withits own French activities, in its consumer products division. REUTER&#3;